Golden Duck is now a skeleton grab n go operation from the pandemic. My spouse and I, regular patrons, received food poisoning after consuming two of their dishes.  The food was mushy, tasted a little strange and wasn't fresh.  Lab results indicate camphybac bacteria.  Consumers beware.
Their duck noodle is very good, but dining in is not possible so I made a mess trying to finish it in the car. Still its very good.

Great find in the area!  There is a small parking lot behind the building which is great given street parking is tough around here.  Wait times vary wildly. I came here with a friend, we both ordered at the same time. His order was complete within 5 minutes, versus mine taking nearly 35 minutes!  Portions are rather large, so there is a good value proposition here. Enough to last at least two meals.

Wow!  Really great Cantonese Chinese food with great service and lots of parking at dinner time. We had the Choy Sum (like Spinach) with Oyster Sauce and Soft Gau Gee (Dumplings) Mein (Noodles). Each dish is a huge serving that we ate family style (sharing the dishes). If you're in to the yellow hot mustard with soy sauce used as a dipping sauce, you'll be happy to know it was freshly made and spicy hot. A sure sign of quality Chinese food IMO. The staff kept our tea and water full, one of the important measures of good service.

Ordered take out Sunday evening. Ordered pork with sweet sour cabbage. Couldn't believe when I opened the container to find 5 chunks of hard cabbage cores mixed into the dish. One piece, perhaps a possible mistake. 5 pieces of core, a purposeful method of discarding your inedible garbage. I wouldn't even feed it to my dog. Based on that sad experience, I will never order from Golden Duck again. I hope the restaurant owners read this and see what kind of food their cooks are packing for customers. I always give a place a second chance...and the second time was a terrible as well. Firstly, the prices that you see online, are out dated. So DO NOT think you'll be getting the price you see online, when you go to pick up your food if you're ordering take out, as they charge you a lot more.  My second experience with Golden Duck, is when I ordered 8 pieces of crispy gaugee. I went in, looked in the bag, counted 8 and left. Just a few moments later (two blocks away), I noticed they had not packed the sauce. So I turned around, went back in, and kindly asked for the sauce that should've came with my order. The cashier got really frustrated and began raising her voice at me lol. She then proceeded to insist that two sauces came with my order and that nothing else could be done...I realized the situation and just left.  I don't support any establishment that can care so little for it's customers, let alone flat out accuse a customer of lying. Don't eat there, there are alternative chinese restaurants in the area, that give amazingly better service.
